is there any reason to set if the other is blank? if not then it should look like:
if (StringUtils.isNoneBlank(source.getUserName(), source.getPassword())) { proxyConfig.setUserName(source.getUserName()); proxyConfig.setPassword(source.getPassword()); }
if yes, then you could use StringUtils.isNotBlank

